OL,3,CHow those in power failed to prevent
OL,4,Cthe violent abuse of thousands of
OL,5,Cyoung men
OL,7,FContained in the 200 pages of the
OL,8,Freport into Medomsley Detention Centre
OL,9,Fare the most harrowing truths about
OL,10,Fone of the most disturbing chapters in
OL,11,FBritish justice history.
OL,13,FIn the early 1960s, the idea of a
OL,14,F'short, sharp shock' was popular in
OL,15,Fpost-war Britain; delinquent boys as
OL,16,Fyoung as 16 given a few weeks of
OL,17,Fmilitary style discipline to set them
OL,18,Fback on the straight and narrow.
