OL,3,CHow those in power failed to prevent
OL,4,Cthe violent abuse of thousands of
OL,5,Cyoung men
OL,7,FThe report's author compared it to
OL,8,Fbeing "like something out of the 16th
OL,9,Fcentury".
OL,11,FThen there was the sexual abuse.
OL,12,FNeville Husband, in charge of
OL,13,FMedomsley's kitchens, unmasked in this
OL,14,Freport as "possibly one of the most
OL,15,Fprolific sexual offenders in British
OL,16,Fhistory".
OL,18,FFor years, Husband had free rein to
OL,19,Fpick and choose his victims, which ran
OL,20,Finto the many hundreds.
OL,26,@vD@KOUxD@HO]
