OL,3,CHow those in power failed to prevent
OL,4,Cthe violent abuse of thousands of
OL,5,Cyoung men
OL,7,FNeville Husband was jailed in 2003 for
OL,8,F8 years for the abuse of 5 young men.
OL,9,FHis sentence was increased to 10 years
OL,10,Fafter 4 more victims came forward.
OL,11,FHusband died in 2010 shortly after his
OL,12,Frelease from prison.
OL,14,FLeslie Johnson, a storeman at
OL,15,FMedomsley, was jailed for 6 years in
OL,16,F2005 for sexual offences. He's now
OL,17,Fdead.
OL,19,FFive former prison officers were also
OL,20,Fprosecuted:
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/11
